values ('31abcb82c4bf812e9d07e864e97ca8ee', 'mastinkipp', 'Mastin', 'Kipp', 'm@mastinkipp.com', '4242024941', 'March 5, 2026 2:49 PM', '[{"label":"Who will need to be included in communication about the work we’re doing?","value":"Brogan Benner\nbrogan@mastinkipp.com"},{"label":"Accounting Contact","value":"Mastin Kipp - m@mastinkipp.com"},{"label":"Who is your IDEAL target customer?","value":"Ideal Target Customer:\n\nMy primary audience is what I call \"The Sophisticated Stuck\" — high-achieving professionals, entrepreneurs, and executives (predominantly women, 35–55) who are disciplined, organized, and outwardly successful, but feel emotionally constricted, armored, or unable to access the next level of aliveness, freedom, or fulfillment.\nThese are people who have done extensive personal development work — read the books, attended the seminars, worked with coaches — yet still feel blocked. They are not overwhelmed or in crisis. They are high-functioning, capable, and driven. But their success is being maintained through control and suppression rather than true integration, and that same overcontrol is exactly what''s keeping them from breaking through.\nThey tend to say things like:\n\n\"I''ve done all the work — why am I still stuck?\"\n\"I can do everything, but I don''t feel much.\"\n\"I function well, but I feel tightly wound.\"\n\"I don''t fall apart. I just shut it down.\"\n\"I want to perform without it costing me so much.\"\n\"I know what to do. I just can''t seem to do it consistently.\"\n\nDemographics:\n\nAge: 28–55\nPrimarily women, men also well-represented\nIncome: $75K–$1M+ household income\nEntrepreneurs, executives, coaches, consultants, salespeople, real estate professionals, high-performing business owners\n\nPsychographics:\n\nHigh consumers of personal development (Tony Robbins, Gabby Bernstein, Andrew Huberman, Mel Robbins, etc.) but feel like they''ve hit a ceiling\nValue science-backed, credible approaches — not just motivation or \"woo\"\nWant transformation, not just information\nIntellectually curious and self-aware\nBelieve they have more potential than they''re currently accessing\nCrave a methodology that explains why the other stuff hasn''t worked\n\nCore Pain Points:\n\nPatterns repeating despite doing \"the work\"\nPerforming at a high level but feeling emotionally flat, disconnected, or exhausted\nDisconnected from purpose at the peak of external success\nSustaining success through willpower and control rather than ease and integration\nWant momentum that feels alive — not just productive\n\nWhat They''re Looking For:\n\nA trusted authority who bridges neuroscience, somatic work, and real-world business results\nSomeone with serious credibility AND genuine warmth and depth\nA clear, proven methodology that explains why they''re stuck and gives them a real path forward\nA community of peers at a similar level who get it\n\nWho this is NOT for:\n\nPeople who are currently in emotional crisis, actively overwhelmed, or regularly losing functioning under pressure\nPeople who get flooded, spiral, or shut down when challenged — and haven''t yet built the capacity to hold that activation\nPeople who are still in survival mode financially, emotionally, or relationally\nPeople who need a therapist or trauma stabilization work before they can engage in growth-oriented coaching\nPeople who are primarily drawn to trauma processing, wound-focused work, or deep therapeutic excavation — and are not yet ready for activation and performance-oriented growth\nPeople who resonate primarily with Gabor Maté, Bessel van der Kolk, Scott Lyons, The Holistic Psychologist, or similar teachers whose work focuses on deep trauma healing, nervous system stabilization, and therapeutic recovery — that is important and valuable work, but it is a different season than what this methodology addresses\nPeople who are looking for someone to process their pain with — this work is not talk therapy\nPeople who want to be rescued, held, or endlessly validated rather than challenged and expanded\nPeople who are reactive, impulsive, or emotionally volatile and haven''t yet developed basic self-regulation\nPeople who are still in the process of becoming stable — no consistent income, no stable relationships, no basic life structure\nPeople who are early in their personal development journey and still getting oriented to the basics\nPeople who want quick fixes, hacks, or surface-level motivation without doing real inner work\nPeople who are resistant to somatic or body-based approaches and only want purely intellectual or tactical solutions\nPeople who identify primarily as \"healing\" rather than \"growing\" — if the dominant orientation is still toward recovery and stabilization, this is not the right next step\n\nThe bottom line: This work is designed for people who are already capable and functional — but know there is a deeper level available to them. If you are still working on becoming stable, this is not the right next step. There are incredible resources and practitioners for that season of life — including many of the teachers named above. This is for the person who has done that work, has built a foundation, and is now ready to stop managing their life and start fully living it."},{"label":"Do you have any brand identity or guidelines that you have available for reference? If so, please share the link below:","value":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jq41I18JsXVYxp30X6hNR_Pme2jn_5ns/view?usp=sharing"},{"label":"What are the PAIN points of the customers you help?","value":"Client Pain Points\nIn Their Own Words\nMastin Kipp — Brand Reference Document for Syncrosocial\nDerived from client intake data across multiple program cohorts\n\nWho These Clients Are\nMastin''s clients are what he calls \"The Sophisticated Stuck\" — high-achieving professionals, entrepreneurs, coaches, and executives who are disciplined, capable, and outwardly successful, but feel blocked, constrained, or unable to access the next level of aliveness, performance, or fulfillment.\n\nThey have done extensive personal development work. They are not beginners. They are not in crisis. They are people who have read the books, attended the seminars, worked with coaches, and invested significantly in themselves — and still feel stuck at a ceiling they can''t break through.\n\nThe pain is not that life is falling apart. The pain is that life is working — and it still doesn''t feel like enough. Below are their pain points in their own words, drawn directly from client intake forms.\n\n1. \"I Know What To Do — I Just Can''t Seem To Do It\"\nThe most universal pain across all clients. They have the knowledge, the tools, the frameworks. But the gap between knowing and doing feels impossible to close. They''ve tried everything at the intellectual level and nothing has produced lasting change. This is the pain point that most defines Mastin''s audience and most clearly differentiates his methodology.\n\nTheir exact words\n\"I have a lot of intellectual knowledge of the material — trauma-informed, polyvagal theory, attachment theory. I know my trauma history. I struggle with putting it all together and staying regulated.\"\n\"A lot of the information has become knowledge rather than practice.\"\n\"I''ve done so much healing on myself and not as much performance.\"\n\"I ''know'' a lot… I say it all the time and it doesn''t get me anywhere. I want to start feeling again. I just don''t know how to do it.\"\n\"I''ve completed many online courses but I am not satisfied — not because they have no value — but because I have not applied the lessons.\"\n\"I feel I have great potential and I feel it in my body that I should be more, or I should do more — but somehow I am not getting where to start.\"\n\"I always get a lot out of every program. But the changes are never permanent.\"\n\"I''ve enrolled myself into multiple modalities. NLP, hypnotherapy, psychotherapy, yoga, breathwork, somatics, journaling, DBT, self-compassion, reading self-help books. I need something more practical and sustainable.\"\n\"I have been in the human potential zone for many years. I have completed quite a few courses but somehow I am not satisfied — I always feel like a failure, as if I have not lived according to my potential.\"\n\n2. Self-Sabotage That Defies Logic\nThese clients are acutely self-aware about their self-sabotage — and baffled by it. They watch themselves undermine their own goals in real time and cannot stop it. They don''t need to be told they''re self-sabotaging. They need someone who can explain WHY — and offer a path that goes beneath the mindset layer they''ve already exhausted.\n\nTheir exact words\n\"I enrolled to gain a deeper understanding of why I have been sabotaging my own success. I hope to uncover the root causes of these patterns and develop the tools and mindset necessary to break free from them.\"\n\"I have parts who feel success is unsafe and that I am not good enough to succeed. I may self-sabotage by not sleeping, eating, or hydrating well. I may create narratives that prioritise ''other'' things which will encourage me to not show up and do the work.\"\n\"I''m tired of being miserable, stuck, watching myself repeat the same patterns over and over but feeling powerless to break the cycle. I feel like a giant waste of potential at best.\"\n\"I want to get in control of the things that have been holding me back and stop stumbling at the same places in my life.\"\n\"I''m aware of so many of my ''limiting beliefs'' but have no clue how to change them despite exploring many avenues.\"\n\"My perfectionism, my unrealistic expectations, and my self-sabotaging behaviour.\"\n\"Overthinking, under-doing, and perfectionism.\"\n\"I want to stop self-sabotaging and actively work on achieving my goals.\"\n\"I want to stop defaulting to unworthiness. Self-sabotage is what gets in my way — every single time.\"\n\n3. Hiding, Invisibility, and Fear of Being Seen\nA striking number of clients use the exact word \"hiding.\" They are keeping themselves small — in their business, their content, their relationships, and their lives. This is not shyness. It is a deeply conditioned response to the perceived danger of being fully seen. They want visibility desperately and feel completely unsafe pursuing it.\n\nTheir exact words\n\"I want to feel safe being highly visible, vocal, and impactful. I want to regulate avoidance of judgment and criticism which I have allowed to keep me invisible and unheard.\"\n\"I''ve felt like I''ve been hiding my whole life.\"\n\"I want to learn to self-regulate, discover root causes of lack mentality, self-sabotage, procra"},{"label":"What are the DESIRED OUTCOMES of the customers you help?","value":"Desired Outcomes of Clients\nIn Their Own Words\nMastin Kipp — Brand Reference Document for Syncrosocial\nDerived from client intake data across multiple program cohorts\n\nWho These Clients Are\nMastin''s ideal clients are high-achieving professionals, entrepreneurs, coaches, and executives who are disciplined, capable, and outwardly successful — but feel blocked, constrained, or unable to access the next level of aliveness, performance, or fulfillment.\n\nThey are not in crisis. They are not beginners. They have done the personal development work — the books, the seminars, the therapy, the coaching. They are growth-oriented people who want to operate at a higher level of functioning, freedom, impact, and embodiment.\n\nTheir desired outcomes are not primarily about stopping the pain. They are about becoming someone whose inner world can hold the life they are trying to build.\n\nThe core transformation they want: from controlled competence → fully alive high performance.\n\nThey want the version of themselves that knows what to do, actually does it, sustains it under pressure, and feels internally congruent doing it. Below are their desired outcomes in their own words, organized by the themes that appear most consistently across hundreds of client intake responses.\n\n1. To Finally Close the Gap Between Knowing and Doing\nMore than any other outcome, these clients want knowledge to become embodied action. They have accumulated tools, frameworks, and insights for years. The desired outcome is not more information — it is alignment between what they know and how they actually live and work.\n\nThe identity shift they want: from insight → execution\n\nIn their own words\n\"I want to get the information from my head into my body and apply it long term.\"\n\"I want knowledge that isn''t limited to the cognitive aspect — something I internalize. Wisdom over intelligence.\"\n\"I want to actually implement changes — not just accumulate more knowledge.\"\n\"I want my actions to be aligned with my intentions.\"\n\"I want to follow through with all components of the program and learn the skills to keep my promises to myself and to others.\"\n\"A lot of the information has become knowledge rather than practice. I want that to change.\"\n\"I want to experience inner transformation first hand.\"\n\"I want to live out what I learn.\"\n\"I want confidence implementing what I know — especially as things get harder as I keep leveling up.\"\n\n2. Consistent Execution and Follow-Through — Becoming Reliable to Themselves\nThese clients want to become the kind of person who keeps promises to themselves. Not occasionally. Consistently. The desired outcome is not motivation — it is a nervous system that supports follow-through without constant internal negotiation, resistance, or collapse.\n\nThe identity shift: from someone who starts → someone who executes, sustains, and builds momentum\n\nIn their own words\n\"I want to stop procrastinating and actively work on achieving my goals.\"\n\"I want to follow through with my intentions. I want my actions to be aligned with my intentions.\"\n\"I want to be able to follow through with all components of the program and learn the skills to keep my promises to myself and to others.\"\n\"I want to stop self-sabotaging and reach my full potential.\"\n\"I want to have a concrete plan and start executing it.\"\n\"I want to see myself taking actions I''ve hesitated to do or have been putting off.\"\n\"I want consistent implementation — not just bursts followed by collapse.\"\n\"I want to become the type of person who does what they said they would do.\"\n\"I want to put things I learn into practice — not just file them away.\"\n\n3. A Nervous System That Supports Expansion, Not Limits It\nThese clients want regulation not as emotional relief, but as a performance foundation. They want to be able to grow their business, lead, be visible, take risks, and hold pressure — without their own nervous system becoming the ceiling. Steadiness while expanding is the outcome.\n\nThe identity shift: from a nervous system that caps capacity → one that enables it\n\nIn their own words\n\"To be sturdier in my self-regulation so I can help my clients, build my business, and stop waiting for the other shoe to drop.\"\n\"I want to regulate stress so I can perform better.\"\n\"I want to feel more regulated and capable as I grow.\"\n\"I want a nervous system that can hold the next level of my life.\"\n\"I want to be able to keep leveling up without my system going offline.\"\n\"I want to ride the wave of any emotion and keep moving forward — especially in activating situations.\"\n\"I want to be in neutral. Less internal noise. More capacity to act.\"\n\"I want to be able to feel fear and still move forward.\"\n\"I want to move forward without getting locked into freeze or overwhelm.\"\n\"I want to expand and take new risks — and sustain the new level of discomfort.\"\n\n4. Confidence and Self-Worth That Matches Their Competence\nMany of these clients are already highly capable — but their internal experience of themselves lags beh"},{"label":"What is your PROCESS for helping clients get from where they are to where they want to go?","value":"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1MBvy4eAS6e0MJPppTlToYetegavoI1ys/edit?usp=sharing&ouid=106959303470499140387&rtpof=true&sd=true"},{"label":"Please provide links to some examples of social media clips that you like from a design perspective:","value":"https://www.instagram.com/reels/DSD2oH8kdSb/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DUE7wl_EQNd/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reels/DT3tRgbEQF-/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reels/DUmRL_7Dy7i/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reels/DT5tRboDjef/"},{"label":"Please provide links to video thumbnails/cover images that you like from a design perspective:","value":"https://www.instagram.com/reels/DSD2oH8kdSb/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DUE7wl_EQNd/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reels/DT3tRgbEQF-/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reels/DUmRL_7Dy7i/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reels/DT5tRboDjef/"},{"label":"What font preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs? If you are open to our recommendations, please feel free to mention it below:","value":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jq41I18JsXVYxp30X6hNR_Pme2jn_5ns/view?usp=sharing\n\nOPEN TO SUGGESTIONS AS WELL"},{"label":"What color preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs?","value":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jq41I18JsXVYxp30X6hNR_Pme2jn_5ns/view?usp=sharing\n\nOPEN TO SUGGESTIONS"},{"label":"What would success look like working together?","value":"2% engagement per post of total following\n10% or more follower growth compounding per month"},{"label":"Anything else we should know?","value":"no"}]'::jsonb, 'notion-legacy', '2026-03-05T14:49:00.000Z')
