values ('2f2bcb82c4bf81388c9ff7e99f65cfe3', 'chelseyscaffidi', 'Chelsey', 'Scaffidi', 'chelseyscaffidi@gmail.com', '4193515785', 'January 24, 2026 2:27 PM', '[{"label":"Who is your IDEAL target customer?","value":"Generally, women that are pregnant or in early motherhood.\n\nSpecifically, she is:\n- A woman in her early 30s–early 40s\n- Often a mother (new-ish or in the thick of it), but not only defined by that\n- Educated, thoughtful, and emotionally intelligent\n- Spiritually curious (God-centered or open, but not dogmatic)\n- Drawn to beauty, language, meaning, and naming what feels unnamed\n- A little tired of productivity culture, optimization hacks, and “do more” energy\n- Wants to live a beautiful life — inwardly and outwardly\n- High-functioning on the outside, quietly unraveling or reassembling on the inside because society doesn''t prepare you for birth of having a child. We weren''t raised in villages where we were around a lot of children.\n- My client is likey the kind of woman who has succeeded in the “masculine” world (career, competence) but is now being pulled toward the feminine: intuition, softness, surrender. She is feeling things deeply but lacking language for them"},{"label":"Do you have any brand identity or guidelines that you have available for reference? If so, please share the link below:","value":"https://drive.google.com/file/d/12XqRz4RU-bGWMf410oui4HQFD0JqRtCV/view?usp=sharing"},{"label":"What are the PAIN points of the customers you help?","value":"She is going through a profound internal transformation (matrescence, which is another word for the process of becoming a mother), but the world around her does not recognize it, name it, or make space for it — so she quietly wonders if something is wrong with her. Everything else flows from that.\n\nShe feels:\nDisoriented — “I’m not who I was, but I’m not sure who I am yet.”\nUnmirrored — no language, rituals, or cultural acknowledgment for what she’s in.\nInvisible — especially in motherhood, where the work is constant but unseen.\nSplit — between competence and tenderness, ambition and surrender, structure and softness.\nAlone in it — even when surrounded by people.\n\nThis is what I would call \"matrescence without a map\".\n\nHow that pain shows up day-to-day ~ sounds like:\n“I should be grateful… so why do I feel like I’m grieving something?”\n“I love my children, but I miss myself.”\n“Why does this feel so much bigger than what people told me?”\n“I’m functioning, but I don’t feel like me.”\n“I can’t explain this without sounding ungrateful or dramatic.”\n\nThe deeper wound (this is important)\nHer pain isn’t just emotional — it’s systemic. Motherhood is treated as a lifestyle change, not a neurological, hormonal, and identity reorganization.\nStrength is praised; softness is rushed. Productivity is expected; integration is not supported. The threshold is crossed — but no one says “This is sacred. This is real. This will change you.”\n\nSo she internalizes the struggle."},{"label":"What are the DESIRED OUTCOMES of the customers you help?","value":"When she finds my page, she thinks:\n“Oh. She’s putting words to something I’ve been living.”"},{"label":"What is your PROCESS for helping clients get from where they are to where they want to go?","value":"Naming what is happening (matrescence, thresholds, seasons)\nOffering dignity instead of diagnosis\nGiving her words she can borrow when she doesn’t have her own\nReframing her experience as meaningful, intelligent, and human\nI don’t say: “Here’s how to fix it.”\nI say: “Here’s how to understand it.”\nAnd that alone brings relief."},{"label":"Please provide links to some examples of social media clips that you like from a design perspective:","value":"- https://www.instagram.com/p/DRkvdMLE6QS/\n- https://www.instagram.com/p/DTd9onOCGCj/\n- https://www.instagram.com/p/DS1zz5sjPQV/\n- https://www.instagram.com/p/DTa36BLjM-N/\n- https://www.instagram.com/p/DTinwUHjGBa/\n- https://www.instagram.com/p/DTS_KrtEZgk/\n- https://www.instagram.com/p/DS09X6EgXqb/\n- https://www.instagram.com/p/DTwJUH-Afxu/\n- https://www.instagram.com/p/DPehX-fieOa/"},{"label":"Please provide links to video thumbnails/cover images that you like from a design perspective:","value":"https://www.instagram.com/p/DPdtSxniIxa/?img_index=1\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DPwc098DNCN/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DPzB8dPkVOw/?img_index=4\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DN5Rc6FDra4/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DNi3i6BsePz/\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DQ7w4F8Dmf8/?img_index=1"},{"label":"What font preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs? If you are open to our recommendations, please feel free to mention it below:","value":"I like Cardo and Nord. See example here but I am also open to your recommendations. I just want it to be clean but for example, I have toyed with the idea of adding a font that has more of a \"free hand\" look."},{"label":"What color preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs?","value":"I like white or a really light yellow."},{"label":"Google Drive Link to pictures of yourself","value":"https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/uw8mhfyh69gud3g6ql783/ACl8HsfEwU6P5TB01qX-kzY?rlkey=7vtthr74mzgfu1oswvxamnc0u&st=6zlhhw5t&dl=0"},{"label":"What would success look like working together?","value":"Content that feels natural and embodied, not forced. Clips that capture depth in simple moments — short, thoughtful reflections that translate my writing and thinking into video without flattening it or making it trend-driven.\nConsistency without burnout. A rhythm that supports my life as a mother and working professional, and helps me show up regularly without pressure to constantly “perform.”\nGrowth that is aligned, not viral for the sake of virality. I care more about attracting thoughtful, engaged women than reaching everyone.\nA clear through-line across my page — so my bio, pinned posts, highlights, and clips all tell the same story about who this space is for.\nTrust and collaboration. I want this to feel like a creative partnership where ideas can be shaped together, feedback flows easily, and the work feels spacious and supportive."},{"label":"Anything else we should know?","value":"One additional thing that’s important to me is positioning my work clearly in the matrescence space and as an educator in the field. Alongside reflective and personal content, I want to include educational clips grounded in neuroscience and research, translated in a way that feels accessible and human. My ted talk on matrescence is in March 2026 and my goal is to position myself as an expert in this field to eventually shift policy.\n\nI’m also excited to thoughtfully integrate my book, The Mother Year, as a living body of work rather than something promotional. I’d love to explore simple video formats — such as reading short passages aloud — and highlighting the seasonal framework the book is built around. The book is organized into seasons of motherhood, and I’ve developed and trademarked a broader framework called Seasons of Her, which we could gently weave into the content over time so it becomes a recognizable through-line across my page. Ideally, this all feels cohesive: personal reflection, education, and the book reinforcing one another in a way that builds clarity, credibility, and depth.\n\nI am also a meditation teacher and used to own a meditation studio in LA."}]'::jsonb, 'notion-legacy', '2026-01-24T14:27:00.000Z')
