insert into public.legacy_onboarding (id, slug, first_name, last_name, email, phone, submitted_on, fields, source, created_at)
values ('2dcbcb82c4bf812281eec6b1ce7645d2', 'melissapruett', 'Melissa', 'Pruett', 'heymelissa@meltbymelissa.com', '4806782838', 'January 2, 2026 5:12 PM', '[{"label":"Who will need to be included in communication about the work we’re doing?","value":"None for now but we may want to loop in ENC (my creative agency) when we decide who/how we are posting on social and if we may want any extra assets/branding from them."},{"label":"Who is your IDEAL target customer?","value":"My ideal customer is a conscious, beauty-loving woman who sees self care as a sacred practice rather than a luxury. She values clean, intentional products and experiences that honor both results and well-being, and she’s no longer interested in aggressive beauty, hustle culture, or quick fixes. She is emotionally aware, spiritually curious, and drawn to rituals that help her feel grounded, confident, and at home in her body. She comes to MELT not just to look good, but to feel seen, supported, and deeply nourished. Current customer: 23-45. Right out of college, got their first job and treating themself. Wanting to be using the latest and greatest but the cleanest. Lots of mothers to carve out time for self-care."},{"label":"Do you have any brand identity or guidelines that you have available for reference? If so, please share the link below:","value":"https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/l3374thcyejsr4aalc2rd/melt-2024branddeck-final.pdf?rlkey=je0izr6cbqzomxqgszflc2391&st=bzfwbt4x&dl=0"},{"label":"What are the PAIN points of the customers you help?","value":"1. She feels disconnected from herself and her body.\n\nShe’s busy, overstimulated, and often in go-mode—giving to work, family, or others—and has lost touch with her own needs. Her self care feels inconsistent, rushed, or reactive instead of intentional and restorative. She wants to feel grounded, present, and back in her body, not just “get through the day.”\n\n2. She’s overwhelmed by beauty noise and conflicting advice.\nShe’s confused by trends, influencers, aggressive treatments, and endless products that promise results but don’t feel aligned. She doesn’t know who to trust anymore and is tired of being sold to without education. She wants clarity, simplicity, and honest guidance from someone who understands both science and intuition.\n\n3. Her skin isn’t reflecting how she feels inside (or wants to feel).\nShe may be dealing with acne, inflammation, sensitivity, pigmentation, aging concerns, or postpartum/hormonal shifts. She’s frustrated that her skin feels reactive or unpredictable and that harsh treatments have made things worse. She wants results that support her skin’s long-term health, not quick fixes that compromise it.\n\n4. She craves feeling seen, held, and cared for, not processed.\nShe’s had experiences where beauty services felt transactional, rushed, or impersonal. She wants to feel listened to, remembered, and genuinely supported. She’s looking for a space where care is as important as results, and where her experience matters as much as the outcome."},{"label":"What are the DESIRED OUTCOMES of the customers you help?","value":"Our customers want to feel at home in their bodies again, experience healthy, resilient, glowing skin long-term, gain clarity and confidence in their beauty routines, experience self-care as a ritual rather than an obligation, age with power, grace, and self-trust, feel seen, remembered, and deeply cared for, prioritize themselves without guilt, and use beauty as a way to support their evolution and identity."},{"label":"What is your PROCESS for helping clients get from where they are to where they want to go?","value":"THE MELT METHOD\nA holistic beauty ecosystem for skin, body, and self\nMELT is not defined by a location—it’s defined by how we care. Whether someone experiences us through an in-studio service, an online order, a video, or an educational moment, they are entering the same intentional process designed to help them soften, reconnect, and thrive.\n\n1. We Begin with Reconnection (Presence Before Product)\nOur work always starts by bringing people back into relationship with themselves. Through our spaces, our language, our videos, and our rituals, we invite slowing down, tuning in, and softening the nervous system. Before we ever recommend a service or product, we prioritize presence—because real beauty begins with regulation, safety, and self-trust.\nThis happens in-studio, on camera, and at home.\n\n2. We Lead with Education + Discernment (Truth Over Trends)\nWe are deeply committed to clean, non-toxic, integrity-led beauty. We educate our community on ingredients, skin health, and long-term care—cutting through misinformation, trends, and fear-based marketing. We don’t overwhelm; we clarify, empowering people to make informed choices that align with their values and their bodies.\nEducation is the bridge between overwhelm and confidence.\n\n3. We Create Experiential Care (Beauty as Ritual)\nFor those who enter our studios, services are never transactional. They are fully experiential, premium, and ritualized—designed to nourish both skin and nervous system. For those at home, our products and guidance are crafted to turn daily routines into moments of devotion. Every touchpoint is designed to feel intentional, sensory, and supportive.\nWhether it’s a facial, a serum, or a video—care is felt, not rushed.\n\n4. We Offer Clean, High-Integrity Tools (Support That Works)\nOur products are not filler or trend-driven—they are tools. Clean, effective, non-toxic formulations chosen and created to support skin health, resilience, and longevity. They are designed to work synergistically with professional treatments or stand powerfully on their own for those who may never visit a studio.\nWe only offer what we truly believe in and use ourselves.\n\n5. We Build Relationship, Not Dependency (Guidance Over Control)\nWe don’t aim to create dependence on constant treatments, endless products, or external validation. Instead, we build meaningful, long-term relationships rooted in trust, education, and support. We want our community to feel confident, capable, and connected—whether they see us monthly, watch our videos, or simply incorporate our products into their lives.\nOur goal is empowerment, not attachment.\n\n6. We Support Evolution (Beauty That Grows With You)\nSkin changes. Bodies change. Lives change. We honor that. MELT is designed to support people through seasons—hormonal shifts, motherhood, healing, aging, reinvention—without shame or pressure. Our process adapts as our community evolves, offering care that meets people where they are and where they’re going.\nBeauty is not static. Neither are we.\n\nTHE BIG PICTURE PROMISE\nMELT is a multi-touchpoint ecosystem that:\n- Educates without overwhelming\n- Nourishes without harm\n- Beautifies without erasure\n- Supports without dependency\n- Evolves without losing integrity\n\nMELT’s process is a holistic beauty ecosystem rooted in education, clean non-toxic care, and meaningful relationship. Whether experienced through in-studio services, online products, or founder-led content, our approach prioritizes nervous system regulation, long-term skin health, and empowered self-care. We combine premium, experiential treatments with thoughtful education and high-integrity products to support beauty as a ritual—one that evolves with each person’s life, body, and values."},{"label":"Please provide links to some examples of social media clips that you like from a design perspective:","value":"I love Baya''s videos you guys have created.\n\nI''m super inspired by Jamie Sea''s page and I''m obsessed with her aesthetic + inspirational content: https://www.instagram.com/reel/DLaxEu_ROGx/?igsh=MW1ka2lkN3Brajg5Zg==\n\nI also love what Jenay Rose has done on her page. It''s super busy \"maximalist\" but her videos are very engaging and unique: https://www.instagram.com/jenayroseofficial?igsh=bGpsZXE1OXdreWVm\n\nOk, a little different but this is a hair influencer I love. She just absolutely crushes it with her hair care demos and does a ton of simple green-screen videos talking about products and pro tips: https://www.instagram.com/abbeyyung?igsh=bmM3Y2dkd29hOGg4\n\nMy creative agency ENC absolutely crushes from a full-feed design perspective: https://www.instagram.com/encagency?igsh=YWZmbWtjeHk4aHY4\n\nMelissa Wood Tepperberg is by far one of my favorite follows: she is gorgeous, uplifting/inspiring, authentic, and doesn''t take herself too seriously. She is obviously \"always selling\" but never in a salesy way: https://www.instagram.com/melissawoodtepperberg?igsh=OXdzNmtubWhsemYx"},{"label":"Please provide links to video thumbnails/cover images that you like from a design perspective:","value":"I LOVE Jess Winterstern''s cover images with the mixed fonts for each video: https://www.instagram.com/thefeminineheart?igsh=emJrZWp6OXh1dnIw\n\nBasically ALL of Jamie Sea''s cover images/thumbnails are bomb dot com: https://www.instagram.com/jamieseaofficial?igsh=dmJvZ3huNHh5a3Ex\n\nMelissa Wood Tepperberg has so many great vids/cover images:\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DS5SzfJkSFy/?igsh=MmpnZmRrYW50dDVr\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DSuqkR_DX59/?igsh=MWQzZTY1eG1ueHk3cA=="},{"label":"What font preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs? If you are open to our recommendations, please feel free to mention it below:","value":"Open to suggestions here and my creative team uses a lot of mixed fonts on our melt feed. I can ask them for a handful of them and I know our main brand fonts are Lufga and Playfair Display."},{"label":"What color preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs?","value":"I''m definitely open here. We use a lot of white font on the feed as well and we do mix in some of our \"Ceremonial Cream\" and various pink Pantones. We are planning to revamp our brand kit a tad this quarter to hone in on a more mauvey pink Pantone as the core brand color with more cream."},{"label":"Google Drive Link to pictures of yourself","value":"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1YjGWEdRRsRrRJuIANwioF5z_Csqd9AlC?usp=share_link"},{"label":"What would success look like working together?","value":"Success looks like me consistently showing up from the heart—using my voice to educate, inspire, and connect—while nurturing a community that feels seen and supported. Together, we’re creating content that establishes me as a trusted thought leader in my industry while allowing me to geek out on all the things I’m genuinely obsessed with."},{"label":"Anything else we should know?","value":"Thanks so much!"}]'::jsonb, 'notion-legacy', '2026-01-02T17:12:00.000Z')
