values ('303bcb82c4bf8116ba7ed5c4e31ff060', 'daniellerobin', 'Danielle', 'Robin', 'daniellekrobin@gmail.com', '4154205111', 'February 9, 2026 9:06 PM', '[{"label":"Who will need to be included in communication about the work we’re doing?:","value":"N/A"},{"label":"Accounting Contact:","value":"N/A"},{"label":"Who is your IDEAL target customer?:","value":"Adults 30–50, often navigating dating or relationships after a significant life transition (divorce, moving, breakups, giving birth, etc). Or, adults who have identified challenges with dating and relating due to: personal blocks, fatigue around being single, challenges with online dating, self confidence and esteem issues, etc)\n\nSmart, capable professionals (founders, leaders, creatives, entrepreneurs, high-functioning individuals who work for start ups or larger companies.)\n\nNot necessarily steeped in “self-work,” but open, reflective, and growth-oriented. Likely has some experience with personal development or is at the beginning of their journey\n\nCould be doing well externally, but experiencing uncertainty or friction in dating and connection that is impacting other areas of their lives. Or, dating/connection/relationships are their biggest pain point/ the thing they “cant figure out”\n\nResponds best to content that feels calm, precise, human, and real, not performative or preachy, or too woo woo. Wants to learn and absorb information. Values big ideas and tip and tools to apply to their relationships and personal lives. Values clarity, emotional intelligence, and grounded confidence over trends or hot takes"},{"label":"Do you have any brand identity or guidelines that you have available for reference? If so, please share the link below:","value":"Here is the evolution of my brand colors and fonts… but im honestly open to a new direction! https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1TpxGDII1dV6XHhNVgFLia-IOSofAQ3aV?usp=sharing"},{"label":"What are the PAIN points of the customers you help?:","value":"In dating…\nReading signals\nTrouble with boundaries\nDating etiquette\nLoss of self-trust, and also dealing with learning how to trust other people\nDating app fatigue, addiction, burnout\nInability to represent themselves, talk about themselves\nCommunication skills for early connections\nDeveloping clarity around dating and connection goals\nFear of vulnerability (and also fear of not being vulnerable enough)\nTiming pressure, comparison, anxiety related to life stage and age\nDating in nontraditional ways (with children, post divorce, in later years)\nFears around starting over and relearning dating culture\nSpotting red flags\n\nIn relationships (new or established)\nMisalignment & erosion- from time, or lack of communication\nResentment buildup\nEmotional disconnection\nConflict & repair issues: conflict avoidance, or not knowing how to repair\nLoss of aliveness, desire, play, curiosity\nEmotional labor/initiation imbalance\nChallenging attachment dynamics\nSelf-abandonment & identity drift- Losing touch with themselves\n\nIn other areas of life/general\nNavigating how to organize time/time management\nCommunication support in all areas of life\nSelf esteem, confidence, positivity\nCreating consistency, breaking through challenging or stuck phases\nSetting boundaries\nNavigating life transitions\nDealing with rejection\nMaking powerful decisions\nShifting into more open and positive mindsets"},{"label":"What are the DESIRED OUTCOMES of the customers you help?:","value":"Dating:\nBetter matches and a better overall dating experience\nUsing their time and energy well in dating (not wasting on the wrong people)\nMore confidence, self trust\nBetter communication\nAbility to say no to things that dont work\nCalm anxiety\nGet needs met\nAssess potential partners accurately, discernment\nNot bring old patterns into new relationships\nHave fun in the process\nLearn and apply lessons from experiences\n\nRelationships:\nSecure attachment, or reduction of attachment challenges\nHealthy polarity, balance of masculine/feminine energies\nPractices for intimacy, closeness\nMastery of healthy conflict and repair\nBalanced emotional labor, feeling met\nFeeling chosen, desired\nOriented towards growth for both parties and the relationship\nA plan and direction for the future\n\nGeneral:\nA balanced life- Understanding of how to manage all the pieces\nAbility to have hard conversations\nAbility to regulate emotions\nMore confidence and self trust overall\nA sense of direction, a plan, understanding of where things are going"},{"label":"What is your PROCESS for helping clients get from where they are to where they want to go?:","value":"It’s bespoke for each client - happy to dive deeper into this, but here are some core ways I work with people:\n\nFind total clarity: on what’s been blocking them + On what they want /desires/needs\nImprove/shift mindset\nImprove/shift skillset\nCome up with a plan\nPractice in real time\nProvide very close support and tweaking of skillset and mindset as needed to keep them on the path of progress\nGet them to a place where they can sustain the new way of being"},{"label":"Please provide links to some examples of social media clips that you like from a design perspective:","value":"I love https://www.instagram.com/madelynmoon/ - natural but clean and professional, I love that she’s in a home environment, her body positioning, her clothing, she doesnt look too done up. there are many on her page. I like that these are clear and direct, like the editing as well. But there is still a softness. I like the lighting a lot.\nExamples\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DSSjuECkXCj/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DRxB67BkU0r/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==\n\nI like https://www.instagram.com/juliayorks/ - I like what she does with the coffee mug, I like the at home but still professional, Ii like the angles, the lighting. Feels relatable and easy to watch.\nExamples\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DRu4dB3j7Es/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DURiKz5jbXi/?hl=en\n\nNext is - https://www.instagram.com/sarahbcoaching the huge mic feels too formal and i dont love it, but the contrast with the living room makes it nice, and I like her styling, she feels very relatable and also knowledgeable. I like the different angles in these videos.\nExamples\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DUUZWUZkR3z/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA=="},{"label":"Please provide links to video thumbnails/cover images that you like from a design perspective:","value":"I love these from https://www.instagram.com/madelynmoon/ with the contrasting word in another color, and I like that they are all flattering!\nExample here\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DTslM97EcPG/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==\n\nFor an example of what I mean by “not flattering”:\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DTJVV65gqdK/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==\n\nI love the font she uses https://www.instagram.com/msrachelhollis and though im less a fan of “cover photos” (that are in a different setting than the video) I like how she does them- hers are natural and I like that she uses a mix (some are photos of her in other environments, some are in the same setting as the video.\nExample here and here (the two different types)\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DS0JA1ij7O2/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DSBCsLUE0Za/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==\n\nFor an example of what I feel is “unnatural”:\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DTswX2Kigx4/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==\n\nAnother one I like a lot is https://www.instagram.com/sarahbcoaching I love the use of the two fonts here her photos feel a little… same same but I like the general direction of it all.\nExample\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DUX-8szE-KM/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA=="},{"label":"What font preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs? If you are open to our recommendations, please feel free to mention it below:","value":"Open to your recs! You''ll see some fonts in my brand folder and I also mentioned some I like in the example links I just shared above"},{"label":"What color preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs?:","value":"I''d love to keep it in line with the rest of the brand/vibe, open to your thoughts! White would work better than yellow."},{"label":"Google Doc Link to links to podcast, speeches or any other video content you want us to create content from:","value":"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1_cFI8iBjH3fMCkN8UeZIaccRVSdM5xZ3?usp=sharing"},{"label":"What would success look like working together?:","value":"Increased reach! Followers, views, engagement, comments, shares (I don''t know numbers because I dont really know what''s possible)\nNew 1:1 client inquiries\nAudience engagement to the point where I''ll feel ready to launch or sell a program\nPromoting a lead magnet to increase email list and provide more value to followers\nFully establishing new brand and voice!\nOutreach for other opportunities (speaking, writing, podcast, collaborations)"},{"label":"Anything else we should know?:","value":"Re: photos of me....Let’s talk about this! I don''t really have photos that are not mirror selfies, selfies of my face, in some costume or clearly meant for a dating app…or with a ton of other friends in them."}]'::jsonb, 'notion-legacy', '2026-02-09T21:06:00.000Z')
