values ('2e6bcb82c4bf818dab14f045f34d3ea5', 'davidkessler', 'David', 'Kessler', 'david@grief.com', '213-700-8702', 'January 12, 2026 3:40 PM', '[{"label":"Who will need to be included in communication about the work we''re doing?","value":"Zach Taylor, zach@grief.com, 434-242-8697"},{"label":"Accounting Contact","value":"David Kessler, david@grief.com"},{"label":"Who is your IDEAL target customer?","value":"Our Ideal Customer\nOur ideal customer is someone who has had a loved one die and is seeking compassionate, understanding support. They may feel isolated in their grief or disconnected from people in their lives who don''t fully understand what they''re going through.\nThey often long for a safe space where they can share their story without judgment and connect with others who \"get it.\" They value kindness, authenticity, and a community where vulnerability is welcomed.\nAlso includes people who have experienced other kinds of losses such as divorce, however our primary audience would be around the death of a loved one.\n\nDemographics:\nAdults aged 35–70, though we welcome younger and older adults as well\n\nPredominantly women, but we are committed to supporting people of all genders\n\nOften reside in the U.S., Canada, or English-speaking countries, but we have a growing international community\n\nVaried educational backgrounds, from high school graduates to advanced degrees\n\nDiverse economic situations; some are professionals, others are retired, or currently unable to work due to grief or caregiving responsibilities\n\nCommonly include parents who have lost children, spouses who have lost partners, adult children grieving parents, and people grieving siblings, friends, or pets"},{"label":"Do you have any brand identity or guidelines that you have available for reference? If so, please share the link below:","value":"Need email address of person/people to share the Google Drive with. There is no public link. Please share."},{"label":"What are the PAIN points of the customers you help?","value":"Our customers are in grief. They are struggling to understand what they are feeling, and how to get through the pain. Most of us are grief illiterate and find it difficult to put words to what we''re going through when we experience a loss. They are often feeling very alone and isolated."},{"label":"What are the DESIRED OUTCOMES of the customers you help?","value":"They want to reduce their emotional pain and find a way to move forward after loss."},{"label":"What is your PROCESS for helping clients get from where they are to where they want to go?","value":"We have some of the largest online grief support groups called Tender Hearts and we also have a Certified Grief Educator program for those who want to learn to help others in grief. We will also be adding more online courses to our catalogue as well."},{"label":"Please provide links to some examples of social media clips that you like from a design perspective:","value":"Please see David''s current page, particularly those posted from podcasts he''s done, like Mel Robbins.\n\nI do really like what you''ve done with Baya Voce''s account as well."},{"label":"Please provide links to video thumbnails/cover images that you like from a design perspective:","value":"https://www.instagram.com/reel/DSaHOXtEliM/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link&igsh=MzRlODBiNWFlZA=="},{"label":"What font preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs? If you are open to our recommendations, please feel free to mention it below:","value":"These are in our branding folder that we will share."},{"label":"What color preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs?","value":"Also in our branding folder."},{"label":"What would success look like working together?","value":"We''d like to focus on opt-ins to our email list and new customer acquisition first, then high engagement, then follower growth. Unless you have other advice."},{"label":"Anything else we should know?","value":"Most of our video content is in Wistia - we will share that link with you soon.\n\nPlease let us know what email is best to use to grant access to our login links, Wistia link, and branding folder."}]'::jsonb, 'notion-legacy', '2026-01-12T15:40:00.000Z')
