values ('348bcb82c4bf8104833cd31358d7fb35', 'terrinammar', 'Terrin', 'Ammar', 'terrinammar@gmail.com', '7758460864', 'April 20, 2026 12:13 AM', '[{"label":"Who will need to be included in communication about the work we’re doing?","value":"For now just myself and Henry.\nHenry@Henryammar.com"},{"label":"Accounting Contact","value":"terrinammar@gmail.com"},{"label":"Who is your IDEAL target customer?","value":"My ideal target customer is a high-achieving, emotionally intelligent, growth minded woman who is married or in a long-term relationship (or desires a relationship with a masculine man) and feels like she’s carrying the weight of the relationship.\n\nShe is successful in her career or business. She''s a \"doer.\" She’s used to leading, solving problems, and holding everything together in her business and at home which is the problem. Planning, doing, moving things forward. On the outside, her life looks put together but inside her relationship, she feels exhausted, disconnected, and sometimes resentful. She doesnt want to be the one carrying everything all the time and wishes her husband would step up and lead.\n\nShe doesn’t actually want to be “the masculine one”…\nShe just doesn’t feel safe enough to let go of control and step into her feminine.\n\nShe craves:\n– To feel soft, desired, and pursued again (to embody her feminine)\n– A husband who leads, shows up, and creates emotional safety\n– Deep connection, intimacy, and partnership\n– To relax without everything falling apart\n\nShe is not looking for traditional therapy, surface-level communication tips, or mindset-only work. She most likely has tried all that.\n\nShe is drawn to:\n– Nervous system regulation\n– Somatic / embodiment work\n– Feminine-masculine polarity\n– Real transformation that actually shifts the dynamic in her marriage\n\nShe is self-aware, invested in growth, and willing to invest at a high level ($5K–$25K+) for real, lasting change. Rich buyer psychology.\n\nShe resonates with bold, direct, emotionally activating content that:\n– Content that describes what she''s feeling and experiencing better than she can\n– Calls her out (without shaming her)\n– Deeply understands her experience\n– Shows her a new way she hasn’t tried before\n– Helps her understand the masculine psyche\n\nShe is the woman who says:\n“I’ve done the work… but my relationship still doesn’t feel the way I know it could.”"},{"label":"Do you have any brand identity or guidelines that you have available for reference? If so, please share the link below:","value":"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1BRJRzGVkc5313XrnCJHkzHbDo7wCTzVF?usp=sharing"},{"label":"What are the PAIN points of the customers you help?","value":"My ideal client’s core pain points revolve around feeling like she is carrying the relationship while deeply wishing she didn’t have to.\n\nShe experiences:\n– Emotional exhaustion from always being “on” and in control\n– Feeling like the leader in the relationship instead of being led\n– A loss of attraction, polarity, and intimacy with her husband\n– Disconnection, tension, or resentment that keeps repeating\n– Feeling unseen, unappreciated, or unsupported\n– A lack of emotional safety that keeps her guarded and hyper-aware\n\nShe often says things like:\n“I wish I didn’t have to carry everything.”\n“I just want him to step up without me having to ask.”\n“Why do I feel like the one holding this whole relationship together?”\n“I don’t want to be in control all the time… I just don’t know what happens if I let go.”\n“I love him, but something feels off.”\n“I don’t feel like I can fully relax.”\n\nShe may also struggle with:\n– Overthinking, control, or hypervigilance in the relationship\n– Shutting down, pulling away, or reacting emotionally\n– Wanting more leadership, presence, and initiative from him—but feeling like she has to manage or direct everything\n– Feeling confused because traditional solutions (therapy, communication tools, date nights) haven’t created lasting change\n\nAt a deeper level, her biggest pain is:\nShe doesn’t feel safe enough to soften…\n…and she doesn’t trust that if she stops holding everything together, he will rise to meet her."},{"label":"What are the DESIRED OUTCOMES of the customers you help?","value":"My ideal client’s desired outcomes are to feel deeply held, desired, and supported in her relationship—without losing her power or identity.\n\nShe wants:\n– To feel safe enough to soften and relax in her relationship\n– To no longer feel like she has to carry everything or be in control\n– A husband who naturally steps up, leads, and takes initiative\n– To experience strong masculine presence, direction, and emotional steadiness\n– To feel pursued, chosen, and deeply desired again\n\nShe desires a relationship that feels:\n– Calm instead of tense\n– Connected instead of distant\n– Playful, intimate, and alive instead of transactional or routine\n\nShe wants to:\n– Trust her partner to lead without micromanaging him\n– Feel emotionally and physically safe enough to open fully\n– Communicate her needs with softness and confidence instead of pressure or frustration\n– Experience consistent affection, presence, and partnership\n\nAt a deeper level, she desires:\n– To shift out of survival mode and into feminine ease\n– To feel secure, supported, and grounded in love\n– To respect and admire her husband again\n– To create a relationship dynamic where he rises into his masculine and she naturally relaxes into her feminine\n\nUltimately, she wants to say:\n“I don’t feel like I have to hold everything together anymore.”\n“I feel taken care of, desired, and at peace in my relationship.”\n“I didn’t know love could feel like this.”"},{"label":"What is your PROCESS for helping clients get from where they are to where they want to go?","value":"My process is a trauma-informed, science backed, nervous-system-based approach that helps women shift the dynamic of their relationship by first shifting themselves at the deepest level. Ultimately into their feminine essence to inspire masculine leadership.\n\nI don’t focus on fixing the man or teaching surface-level communication tools or surface level feminine energy.\n\nI focus on helping the woman regulate her nervous system, understand and release patterns of control and hypervigilance, and return to her embodied feminine state.\n\nThis is done through my I.L.E. Framework: Identify → Liberate → Embody\n\nI – Identify\nWe identify the unconscious patterns driving her relationship dynamic—over-functioning, control, emotional reactivity, and hypervigilance.\nShe begins to see clearly how she has been carrying the relationship and why she hasn’t felt safe enough to let go.\n\nL – Liberate\nThrough trauma-informed, somatic, and nervous system work, she releases the patterns keeping her stuck in survival mode.\nThis is where we dissolve the need to control, reduce emotional charge, and create real safety in her body—not just intellectual understanding.\n\nE – Embody\nShe learns how to live and show up from a grounded, soft, receptive feminine state.\nThis isn’t performative—it becomes her new baseline.\n\nFrom this place, she naturally:\n– Relaxes instead of controls\n– Expresses instead of suppresses or reacts\n– Invites masculine leadership without force\n\nAs she shifts, the relationship shifts.\n\nHer partner begins to respond differently—often stepping into more leadership, presence, and direction—because the dynamic itself has changed.\n\nThe result is not just better communication—it’s a complete transformation of the emotional and energetic dynamic of the relationship.\n\nThis is why my work creates results that traditional therapy or mindset work alone often cannot.\n\nThis is also the work that affects her role as a mother as well... so her children see the kind of marriage that she would want them to have as well as lower her reactivity as a mother with them and have a softer leadership."},{"label":"Please provide links to some examples of social media clips that you like from a design perspective:","value":"https://www.instagram.com/reel/DIzo_aGTsJp/?igsh=eWd5eG5kcWpuOXJy\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DVGnjtYEgKp/?igsh=Zm5uNzZ2OXBhemdv\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DPjCePUEcM3/?igsh=a3BsMHpuNnlnd3Zs\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DV1Rfgoj7Pe/?igsh=NHpxN3Fua3ltbjhx\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/reel/DTfya77D4IU/?igsh=MTl4M3N3ZnRraTNkdg=="},{"label":"Please provide links to video thumbnails/cover images that you like from a design perspective:","value":"I am open to suggestion on this one. On instagram covers I like using my professoinal photos or like a BTS photo for the cover."},{"label":"What font preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs? If you are open to our recommendations, please feel free to mention it below:","value":"This are in my style guide however is elegant fonts like Playfair display, Times New Roman with Italics, just elegant feel."},{"label":"What color preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs?","value":"Refer to designs. mainly blush pinks, black, gold, and neutrals"},{"label":"Google Drive Link to pictures of yourself","value":"https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/gwz6ovpeqknxn8xzr383c/AMir5nYNb1RjzcovJrLZC-s?rlkey=ah4qrdv657i787obrvmlnjors&st=9mt8gxrw&dl=0"},{"label":"What would success look like working together?","value":"Success working together looks like consistent, high-quality content that deeply resonates with my ideal client and converts into qualified leads for my high-ticket offers. Of course growing my reach is a key component but to the right people.\n\nSpecifically:\n\n– Talking head reels with strong, disruptive hooks that stop the scroll\n– Content that clearly speaks to my ideal woman’s pain, desires, and lived experience\n– Messaging that positions me as the authority in feminine embodiment, nervous system work, and relationship dynamics, love energetics & polarity\n\nFrom a growth and conversion standpoint, success looks like:\n– Consistent audience growth with aligned followers (not just numbers)\n– High engagement (saves, shares, comments) from my ideal client\n– Increased inbound DMs from women who feel deeply seen and want to work with me\n– Warm, qualified leads entering my funnel (guides, waitlists, offers)\n– Content that naturally filters out the wrong audience and attracts high-level buyers\n\nAt a deeper level, success is:\n– My content clearly communicates the depth and uniqueness of my work\n– My brand feels elevated, premium, and differentiated in the market\n– My messaging consistently calls in women ready for $5K–$25K+ transformation\n\nUltimately, success looks like:\nMy content doing the heavy lifting, building trust, authority, and desire so that selling becomes natural and clients come in already activated and ready."},{"label":"Anything else we should know?","value":"I asked my AI to help me out with this since it is obviously trained for my content, brand and my goals as well as knows results from data driven information on my content. Its a bit more pointed than me haha but good insights.\n\nA few important things to know so you can win with me:\n\n– Depth over fluff always.\nMy content performs best when it is emotionally activating, deeply resonant, and speaks to what women are actually experiencing but don’t know how to say. Surface-level tips or trendy content will not work for my brand while also being easy to understand.... not woo woo. The QK is the bridge from the woo woo world to the mainstream/modern.\n\n– Hooks are everything.\nMy highest-performing content uses disruptive, pattern-interrupt hooks—especially using words like masculine, feminine, marriage, wife, husband. I want content that makes the right woman feel instantly seen.\n\n– Speak to high-level women.\nMy audience is not beginners. These are self-aware, high-achieving women who have already “done the work.” The content should reflect that level of intelligence and life experience while still being simple and clear.\n\n– I sell transformation, not information.\nEverything should point toward identity shifts and real relationship change, not just advice. My work is somatic, nervous-system-based, trauma informed and embodiment-focused. That distinction needs to be clear in the content. I have been trained by some of the best in this space including Mastin Kipp and Dr Frank Anderson.\n\n– Premium positioning matters.\nI sell $5K–$25K+ offers. The content should feel elevated, clean, powerful, and not mass-market or gimmicky. I would rather have fewer, highly aligned viewers than go viral to the wrong audience.\n\n– My voice is bold, direct, and emotionally honest while at the same time as a feminine feel as well. I am not afraid to lovingly call women forward, but never in a shaming or blaming way. My messaging deeply honors men and masculinity. It should feel like truth, clarity, and leadership not harshness.\n\n– Content should convert, not just perform.\nWe are optimizing for saves, shares, and DMs from the right women... not vanity metrics. Every piece of content should have a purpose in moving someone closer to working with me. I like it to be real and Authentic as well.\n\n– Consistency + strategy = everything.\nI’m looking to build a system where content consistently brings in qualified leads, grows my audience with aligned women, and supports my high-ticket offers without me needing to constantly “sell.” The overall goal is impact above everything else. The more reach the more impact on women, couples and marraiges.\n\n– Big picture goal:\nTo build a category-defining brand in the relationship space for high-achieving women and scale to multiple six figures/month through aligned content, offers, and messaging.\n\nThank you so much Kasper and team. Looking forward to this!"}]'::jsonb, 'notion-legacy', '2026-04-20T00:13:00.000Z')
