values ('37bbcb82c4bf81ffb48ff286c9ef1f24', 'alaynabellquist', 'Alayna', 'Bellquist', 'alaynabellquist@gmail.com', '619-322-7421', 'June 10, 2026 9:07 AM', '[{"label":"Who will need to be included in communication about the work we’re doing?","value":"Just me."},{"label":"Accounting Contact","value":"Me."},{"label":"Who is your IDEAL target customer?","value":"Lyme patients, chronic illness patients, medical community (western and holistic), outdoor enthusiasts, hiking community, hunters, horseback riders, nature-lovers, environmentalists."},{"label":"Do you have any brand identity or guidelines that you have available for reference? If so, please share the link below:","value":"https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/onvmeix4ujrqpucoo9lhv/Alayna-Bellquist-Brand-Bible.pdf?rlkey=itfmupt5m91g788bi872xxqb0&st=pzsqssyi&dl=0"},{"label":"What are the PAIN points of the customers you help?","value":"Physical Pain Points:\nThey have tried treatment after treatment and still don''t feel well.\nThey are exhausted by managing symptoms all day.\nThey live in fear of setbacks, flares, relapses, and reinfection.\nTheir life has become organized around illness.\nThey feel trapped in a body they no longer trust.\nThey have lost the activities they love (hiking, exercise, travel, socializing, work).\nEmotional Pain Points:\nThey are terrified this might be permanent.\nThey feel hopeless after years of trying.\nThey are exhausted by constantly thinking about Lyme.\nThey are angry at their body.\nThey are angry at nature.\nThey are angry at doctors, medical system.\nThey feel isolated and misunderstood.\nThey feel like they are grieving the person they used to be.\nIdentity Pain Points:\nThis is where my work is especially different.\nMy audience often:\nHas unconsciously adopted the identity of a chronic Lyme patient.\nMeasure success by symptom management rather than full recovery.\nHas been taught to expect remission instead of cure.\nHas built a life around avoiding symptoms.\nHas forgotten who they are outside of illness.\nBelief Pain Points:\nThese are arguably the biggest ones I address.\nMany people arrive believing:\n\"My body is broken.\"\n\"Ticks are the enemy.\"\n\"Nature harmed me.\"\n\"I will always have chronic Lyme.\"\n\"The best I can hope for is remission.\"\n\"Healing is mostly about pills and protocols.\"\n\"Recovery depends on finding the perfect treatment.\"\nMy work challenges every one of those beliefs.\n\nIf I had to boil my entire brand down to one core problem: They no longer believe full recovery is possible for them. Everything else flows from that.\nI am not really selling Lyme education. I am helping people move from: \"How do I manage this illness?\" to \"How do I become the kind of person who fully recovers?\" Or even more simply: From surviving Lyme to becoming resilient by nature. Being grateful for Lyme and even better because of it.\n\nThat distinction is what makes my messaging different from almost all other Lyme educators. Most sell information. I sell a new relationship with the body, nature, illness, and recovery itself."},{"label":"What are the DESIRED OUTCOMES of the customers you help?","value":"They don''t just want fewer symptoms. They want to stop organizing their life around illness and start fully living again.\nThey want to:\nFully recover, not just manage Lyme.\nGet their life back.\nHave energy, strength, and freedom again.\nTrust their body instead of fearing it.\nStop worrying about flares, relapses, and reinfection.\nSpend less time thinking about Lyme and more time living.\nReturn to the activities they love, like travel, exercise, nature, work.\nFeel hopeful, confident, and like themselves again.\nReconnect with nature as a source of healing rather than fear.\nBuild a body and life that are more resilient than before they got sick."},{"label":"What is your PROCESS for helping clients get from where they are to where they want to go?","value":"I help people move from chronic illness to full recovery through the 4-Stage Recovery Process (Resilience, ReNature, Regeneration, Rejuvenation).\n\nThis includes:\n- treat the physical illness using appropriate medical and therapeutic interventions.\n- regulate the nervous system and create a sense of safety in the body.\n- address and transform limiting beliefs that keep them stuck in fear, hopelessness, or an illness identity.\n- reconnect with nature''s principles of resilience and recovery to build lasting health and trust in the healing process.\n\nI help people move from fear, symptoms, and chronic illness identity to full recovery by healing the body, regulating the nervous system, understanding deeply held beliefs, and reconnecting with nature."},{"label":"Please provide links to some examples of social media clips that you like from a design perspective:","value":"https://www.instagram.com/p/DXF_yCojg_-/\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DU8mP8CDSD-/\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DYu6-2mPrsA/"},{"label":"Please provide links to video thumbnails/cover images that you like from a design perspective:","value":"https://www.instagram.com/p/DTBRSLaEhH9/\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DUD_gj8D2nb/?img_index=1\n\nhttps://www.instagram.com/p/DS28MWxkqNF/"},{"label":"What font preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs? If you are open to our recommendations, please feel free to mention it below:","value":"See Brand Bible linked above (also open to recommendations)."},{"label":"What color preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs?","value":"See Brand Bible linked above (also open to recommendations)."},{"label":"Google Drive Link to pictures of yourself","value":"https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1zcb11e33f6Qw3fUUlnBaNotyNmuYATEO?dmr=1&ec=wgc-drive-%5Bmodule%5D-goto"},{"label":"What would success look like working together?","value":"Open communication, clear communication, all on the same page. My email list growing consistently every week. Multiple viral/high-performing posts reaching new audiences. Increased workshop/course inquiries and sales. Podcast invitations arriving without outreach. Clear growth/visibility leading into the book launch (September 15, 2026). Fun and pleasant working relationship is really important to me, too :)"},{"label":"Anything else we should know?","value":"SO happy and grateful to get going on this. I am really open to suggestions."}]'::jsonb, 'notion-legacy', '2026-06-10T09:07:00.000Z')
