insert into public.legacy_onboarding (id, slug, first_name, last_name, email, phone, submitted_on, fields, source, created_at)
values ('31fbcb82c4bf81039911c080b1269a85', 'laurentaus', 'Lauren', 'Taus', 'lauren@inbodiedlife.com', '3103392721', 'March 10, 2026 2:17 PM', '[{"label":"Who will need to be included in communication about the work we’re doing?","value":"Jaclyn; you@inbodiedlife.com"},{"label":"Who is your IDEAL target customer?","value":"When I assess my business over the last 5 years, I have two clientele: those who come to me for therapy and those who come to me for clinical training and retreats. The training/retreat client is someone who spends an average of $6k (with me) plus travel expenses and it’s often one time. Although I have more and more retreat participants coming back for their 3rd and 4th times. The therapy client is someone who on average spends about 4x that over the course of a year. For years I’ve not been seeking more therapy clients. So, let’s put this client aside for the time being. I also have therapists that work for me with different specialties and I would love to be able to more fully populate their practices.\n\nMy ideal customer looks much more like those who come on clinical trainings and retreats with me. So, these can be broken down into two profiles:\n\nClinical practitioner: this is someone who is a mental health care practitioner or a doctor and they are interested in psychedelics both as a healing modality for themselves and their clients. They are very open minded, often entrepreneurial and rigorous.\nRetreat goer: this is someone who is usually a self-health junkie or on a healing journey of their own. My population is generally very smart, and successful by material measures.\nBoth populations fall between 25 to 65, with the bulk being 30-50. I serve both men and women, with a split that is likely 30-70 men to women."},{"label":"Do you have any brand identity or guidelines that you have available for reference? If so, please share the link below:","value":"Check my website, but I''m not overly attached since there is some difference between me and my brand. www.inbodiedlife.com"},{"label":"What are the PAIN points of the customers you help?","value":"At a high level, I inspire people through the way I live. At best, that inspiration translates into people wanting to act and looking to my practices and rituals as a path for how to do that.\n\nThe pain points they are experiencing are the natural pain points of the human experience, which is navigating their past or future. Clearing up traumatic experience, learning how to be fully alive and connected."},{"label":"What are the DESIRED OUTCOMES of the customers you help?","value":"People want to feel alive. They want to be in their authenticity and feel good there. People often need help managing their relationships, and I support them with responsible communication skills. Communication is a cornerstone of my practice. I specialize in family work because I find that individual therapy can keep people in the same problematic patterns and loops for an eternity. People need to bring their challenges to the challenging places. I also support people in the development of a spiritual life, of satisfying work. I love to support people in their respective philanthropic work."},{"label":"What is your PROCESS for helping clients get from where they are to where they want to go?","value":"As a therapist, there''s never a one size fits all program. A lot of people come to me for medicine work and I love to speak to this on my platform, but medicine is only in the context of a relationship. Meaning, I need to know the client well. This period of connection is often the preparation period before medicine work, and there will always be integration work afterwards."},{"label":"Please provide links to some examples of social media clips that you like from a design perspective:","value":"I liked the vibe I was working with while I was creating educational content. I also like esther perel, mel robbins, what you have for baya. I don''t really see these accounts as focused on aesthetics much"},{"label":"What font preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs? If you are open to our recommendations, please feel free to mention it below:","value":"I''m open to your recommendations and I liked what I had before, but again I''m open on strategy here"},{"label":"What would success look like working together?","value":"I''d like to grow my following in order to widen my impact and support the development of a bigger brand and body of work. In the future, I can see myself with a podcast and a book. Followings support book deals and sales etc."},{"label":"Anything else we should know?","value":"Lots to discuss for sure.\n\nI''m interested in aliveness, the intersection of science and spirituality, health, and family. I have a lot of different clients for different things. I think we need an onboarding call"}]'::jsonb, 'notion-legacy', '2026-03-10T14:17:00.000Z')
