insert into public.legacy_onboarding (id, slug, first_name, last_name, email, phone, submitted_on, fields, source, created_at)
values ('2e7bcb82c4bf81bfb5e0d1c7f94e1911', 'johnwineland', 'John', 'Wineland', 'jen@johnwineland.com', '818-419-0679', 'January 12, 2026 6:51 PM', '[{"label":"Who will need to be included in communication about the work we''re doing?","value":"Jennifer Vega - we will use her email and phone number as main contact points. Jen will also be the one communicating on Slack. She also needs to be cc''d on all accounting communications and will be doing approvals."},{"label":"Accounting Contact","value":"Ashley Talbot - accounting@johnwineland.com"},{"label":"Who is your IDEAL target customer?","value":"Someone who is willing to let love change how they live, not just how they relate.\nAge: 35–60 - younger is also great, not sure if age is that much of a concern for us.\nIncome: Comfortable to affluent\nAble to invest $3k–$20k+ in workshops and programs and upwards of 100k for private coaching\nLocation: Major cities, progressive or spiritually literate communities\nRelationship status:\nIn long-term partnership and wanting more aliveness\nDivorced or post-divorce and deeply self-reflective\nSingle but no longer casual about intimacy\n\nSome who...\nvalues truth over comfort\nWilling to be challenged\nNot looking for validation\nNot outsourcing responsibility\nCurious about polarity, desire, devotion, presence, embodied leadership in all realms\nThey can sit in discomfort without collapsing or attacking.\n\nThey are relationship-oriented, not performance-oriented\nThey want:\nLove that is alive\nDesire that doesn''t fade\nPolarity that doesn''t rely on roles\nSafety that does not dull eros\nThey sense that intimacy is not about technique, but about how life is met through the body.\n\nWhat They Are NOT\nLooking for trauma-only language\nInterested in pop-psychology relationship tips\nWanting \"masculine/feminine\" as ideology or identity\nConsuming content casually\n\nMen:\nAge: 35–60\nFinancially established (entrepreneur, executive, investor, senior leader)\nHas responsibility for others (company, team, family, lineage)\nIntellectually capable but no longer interested in living from the mind\nOften admired externally, internally restless\nHe does not come for \"men''s work.\"\nHe comes because something in him knows he is not fully inhabiting his depth.\nHe has presence but not always relaxation\nDesire exists but can feel effortful or conditional\nHe is often the stable one, the holder, the provider — and feels alone there\nHe is tired of self-improvement and wants initiation\n\"I''ve done well. Why doesn''t it feel as alive as I expected?\"\nCapacity to stand in love without collapsing\nErotic presence without performance\nLeadership that includes his heart and body\nA masculine path that does not shame softness or neuter power\n\nWomen:\nAge: 30–60\nHighly relational, perceptive, embodied or longing to be\nOften a healer, leader, creative, therapist, coach, or entrepreneur\nHas done deep emotional and spiritual work\nFinancially self-sourced or partnered with significant resources\nShe does not want \"feminine embodiment\" as identity.\nShe wants permission to live from her depth, desire, pleasure and magic\nShe can feel a lot, but not always receive\nDesire is present but often guarded or compartmentalized\nShe has outgrown being \"the strong one\" and also outgrown victimhood\nShe senses that her eros and intuition are meant to lead, not wait\n\"I am done shrinking my desire to protect love.\"\nMoney is not the issue. Being met is.\n\nCOUPLES\nTogether 5–25 years\nFinancially stable or affluent\nNot in crisis, but at a relational edge\nThey have \"worked things out\" but not necessarily opened things up\n\"We don''t want to start over with someone else. We want to go deeper here.\"\nThey are not afraid of investment.\nThey are afraid of wasting it on surface solutions.\nthey wantPolarity without power struggles\nDesire that returns without pressure\nA relational structure that holds eros, truth, and love together\nA shared path that deepens devotion instead of negotiating it"},{"label":"Do you have any brand identity or guidelines that you have available for reference? If so, please share the link below:","value":"This is our current social media brand guide. We have to work on this and will be doing that soon. Any input you have is greatly appreciated. In general, we need to shift things. https://drive.google.com/drive/u/0/folders/1Rxwmpe7LXnz8hE7kzhHcW1ZPuLaXpd_g"},{"label":"What are the PAIN points of the customers you help?","value":"Our current audience is made up of deeply devoted, self-aware practitioners who already trust the work and are actively engaged in it, yet struggle with consistency, integration, and sustainability in their lived experience. They often feel stretched between devotion to practice and the demands of real life, relationships, parenting, leadership, and work, and can experience moments of confusion about how to embody what they know without over-efforting or self-managing. Many carry a sense of responsibility for holding the relational or energetic field, leading to fatigue, self-doubt, or periodic disconnection from pleasure, desire, and aliveness. Their pain is less about not knowing what to do and more about learning how to stay embodied, present, and resourced over time without collapsing, hardening, or abandoning themselves when life intensifies."},{"label":"What are the DESIRED OUTCOMES of the customers you help?","value":"The desired outcome for our current audience is to live in ongoing devotion to truth and to the field of love and life itself, so their practice is no longer something they access in special moments, but a way they consistently meet relationship, leadership, intimacy, and responsibility. They are seeking a felt steadiness in their bodies and nervous systems that allows them to stay present, open, and resourced under real-world pressure, while remaining aligned with what is true rather than what is comfortable. At its deepest level, they want to trust that love, aliveness, and devotion can be lived as a daily orientation, where they are not managing themselves or the field, but participating in life with integrity, responsiveness, and embodied presence over time."},{"label":"What is your PROCESS for helping clients get from where they are to where they want to go?","value":"This is done through workshops, trainings and one-on-one coaching. Our process is around supporting people in healing wounds and staying committed to a consistant practice."},{"label":"Please provide links to some examples of social media clips that you like from a design perspective:","value":"We are really liking what you do with Beya."},{"label":"Please provide links to video thumbnails/cover images that you like from a design perspective:","value":"https://www.instagram.com/p/DL9vaUozUJA/?hl=en&img_index=1\nWe also like nature and real-life clips for our events. We like movement in our posts, something that can capture engagement. We are very big on our transmission."},{"label":"What font preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs? If you are open to our recommendations, please feel free to mention it below:","value":"We use bebes nueue, but we are open to change if it aligns with our transmission."},{"label":"What color preferences do you have or would you like to see in your designs?","value":"This is our color from our logo: #f0675e. I would also look at our website to see the colors John prefers."},{"label":"Google Drive Link to pictures of yourself","value":"https://johnwineland.com/john-wineland-press-information/"},{"label":"Google Doc Link to links to podcast, speeches or any other video content you want us to create content from","value":"https://theembodiedrelationshipexperience.com/podcast/"},{"label":"What would success look like working together?","value":"We would like to see a better branding of our social media, higher numbers and engagement. Can we get to 250k by end of year and bring in new clients who pay? We would like to see a deep increase on our YouTube subscriptions and overall rebranding."},{"label":"Anything else we should know?","value":"There are things here we are revamping and I would like your expertice on. Where are our blindspots, how can we uplevel?"}]'::jsonb, 'notion-legacy', '2026-01-12T18:51:00.000Z')
